TextBlock.TextLine: & b swanskins green streepken to be one pack wrapped with 3 or 4
man chester bayes I observe the hurinour of our custome to be so
indifferent for the cullours in spanish cloathes, that they take allson
if they are butt lovely well bniat & nott dullish where fore in case
you sed a pretty cloth now & then to yd mindes alditt to my parcells
lest 20r 3 of this cullours be gott of 6:6:7 t a 8 st a yd not wist standig
this hard & long continewing winter, I sell now & then some goods, so
that I beleave I shall have little assortement a month hene onelas
yd suply doth come in time. I begine to gett the instomers
advance the prijses in goods so that with the dimninshing of charges
I hope to procure better proffitt I have above £200: for yd acctt
in cash & itt would not do to remitt under 35:6 a 2 uso altohought
itt & generally beleaved that the ex will fall whoever according
toyd ordre am aproviding the gold desired & have part ready, butt
would faine have itt all imployed, & if possible shallyett send itt
forward next friday to mr. coots to follow yd order I exspect to heare
from you & so reman
In Antwarp 4 fer 81
London Henry Collier
th
my last to you was on the 21 past. concerning It an answer there
on is exspected & then mr. Herreyns shall delay no longeratt all, tis don
to give him his full desire, that so. he maiy have no reason to say that
ytt is n exspected in case he beused with forle meanes: I then
promised you the acctt, which my dispositions would not permitt
mee to draw out sence besides have been some dayes aitt brussels butt
god willing if I& do not send y. next saturdayes post then Ile
be blanced, butt that I hope to provent Ben: clarck is arrived &
I beseave the goods att Bruges inhopes to pay butt a small cuttome
as ist is neerly ordered to be demanded, thought itt be not yett pablishd
a bay which p. 45 custome shall pay butt bact according to his valew
rs also a kersie & cottons & cloathes accordingly which if doth take will
augument & ease our gaine in sale I observe yd discretion in writing
of 14 past whert is above shall be pertely in answer, & must
assure you of the sineere inclination I have to prevent yd bills. tis
true you have & while omitted drawing yett thoughtist be the den dest
time of the yeare have payd butt this day £200: for yd bills of
1y gd. now there is butt one more umingon mee of 17 xb £100
be sides £160: flemish mr. forthell drew on mee for yd acctt 8 Jan
a 2 uso which please to not accordingly, which not withstanding
have £150: more which ne thought to have imployd on my bill on y or
for £150 payable to John derichebourght which I would fame have
taken in putte poxon hims he could have 35:10 so in case I can nst
gett itt cheaper p. nextpost, that I should be presented for payement
please to draw the same valew att sight ½ or whold uso as you
finde yd advantidge & can you for beare longes for more Ihope to
sende you some remised very speedly for I asseure you i would
be agreat content. to us both incase I could butt remitt as much
ad you draw the inclosed please dodelicered R which
is safe with you & sore
London Abran Vuvans
In Antwarp 4 feb 1681
th
S my last toyon, was on the 21: past, sethe recd. yd of 10„ 14 & 19 ditto tis
well the £150 were recd. I take not ic of the pattarnes & invoy ces of goods
ready in the north, of N. 24 I want the perfect pattarnboock, which
I naust needs have if there be any this I thinck is now all what was in ordere
thought I could wish you had bought as mony more butt sence that com. he
so much visen wees will see the goods & orderins, I seupose all the bales
bares are att hull & that they shall come with John nelson who is there
ready to saile with first conveniency, our customes & duties shall be
brought to above ½ less then before besides white wares from England
shall not pay above a fiste part, wherefore am more in corridged the
never & hope to promote our advantidge to yd content god be thanked, I have
putt off almost our goods that are here that is to say to the bales N 242 2&
which are att Brayes for the rest is not altogheter 2 bales left msold
you should have hadd all actt before now, butt have been some dayes
in disposed & al most all last week out of towne to provide mony &
have some ready to remitt you butt beleave mee I could gett no bills
att short sight non this 8 dayes under a month, so be confident neatpost
shall boing some, butt you must not be brought to an extremit ie for
you may alwayes in such occasion freely dispose of some monyon
mee by ex. which IC. will not refase, I could not remitted him neother
where fore I desired him to draw £100 on mee for acctt of yd brother
att sight or ½ or whole uso to this advantidge in case wee in coy please
this yeare I do beleave wee shall have a considerable sale, so that I long
to see these goods to governe our selfs accordingly for in may next must
be the beginning of our buying againe: I could wish you had the laces
with you what are already yon for ward N. 6 & 9 is sent by the way of Doued
N.7 bj t driaen block binlander all which I wish were safe to you that
I might understand yd asprobation of them, I have here 2 broad lacesby
mee with more others which I brought a long with mee from
brussels & shall be made up to besent by way of d'over oneles I had yd
contra order the packet N. 8 is still att uruges & so with kinde
shall order N.8 to be sent bij way of Douer & N.10 also to follow the one the
other to venture butt one att a time
In Antwarp 4 fed 1681
London R soutthel
th
S. I was gladd to see yd of 28. past, butt sorrij when I perused the contens
yett hope you ore well ariiced in london o& that you fond all freinds
in good health & wealth pay remember mee to yd all I should have sent
mr. Collier & mr. Anneslay their acctts butt have been not well, & att brussell
for some dayes & the rest of my time on that of H.M4 V fors
cole, so they are gon, this post & those of m. collier & Annes lay shall
follow p next saturdayes: whilst you oe there I could wish you could
endeavour to finde something news & or curious in spanish cloathes
from 10 to 12 a 13 st a yd brought itt shoul be rutt 6 or 8 quarts which
you, la could persuade some body to provide & send mee for his or their
acctt as in collies & annessay, or whom you thinck woul be pleased
to minde itt, for the last in collies sended thought not yett here, are
insteed of such most low prijses & extranagant broad mature
itt beeng the bale f N.36, as you may see by this patt book which
are not to the purpose there fore to wards eastes, or sent rather
